imdb.title: Sukurappudo purinsesu
imdb.plot: The adventures of a princess prophesized to destroy the world and her magic using sibling warrior bodyguards determined to protect her.

episodes.title: The Cast Away Cat Princess' Prelude
episodes.plot: Pacifica is traveling with her cousins. Followers of Mauser want to kill her to stop prophecy that she will destroy world. She meets her aunt Diana.

episodes.title: March of the Half-Baked Knight
episodes.plot: Pacifica, Shannon and Raquel meet Leopold Scorpus, an "errant" Knight who is searching for Doyle Barrett, formerly second in command of the Knight's Errant. Leopold's quest becomes theirs as they seek to understand Pacifica's backstory.

episodes.title: Cacophony of the Unforgivable Fanfare for the Unforgiving Man
episodes.plot: Leopold mistakes the Casull siblings for travelling performers, helping the family to get through a security checkpoint. Danger comes unexpectedly, though, in the form of new assassins.

episodes.title: Deai to Wakare no Concerto
episodes.plot: Shannon rescues Winia from Chris, but not before Chris reveals the truth about Pacifica being the scrapped princess. A new threat lies on the horizon that may prove the worst one yet.

episodes.title: Lullaby of the Minstrel
episodes.plot: A deadly threat, a poisonous sting, a minstrel's song --- and the revelation of Pacifica's true identity to Leopold. But will it all come together in time?

episodes.title: Perplexed Song of the Knights
episodes.plot: Things take a bizarre twist as religion becomes the enemy and Zeferis becomes the blade of Shannon to slay.. - the pope? I am so getting bored by this.

episodes.title: Suteinu Shoujo no Waltz
episodes.plot: God is mistaken, yada yada, The church is correct, yada yada, this show is getting more and more boring as it goes.

episodes.title: Kizuna to Inori no Nocturne
episodes.plot: Pacifica has to -- kill. Cause everyone is a threat, and it's all pretty predictable. Even those who did the subtitles obviously got bored, they can't get a simple name right, calling Cis "Cin" every single time.

episodes.title: Itansha-tachi ni Sasagu Requiem
episodes.plot: The Cassuls discover a hidden town of heretics who hate the Church of Mauser and follow a woman they call the Scrapped Princess. Things only get stranger when a masked man at her side declares this to be the day they fix the world.

episodes.title: Nise Oujo no Serenade
episodes.plot: Lady Elfitine and her people begin a strange ritual with a sinister plot in mind. But something isn't right with the spell. Can the Cassul siblings get to the bottom of the magical mayhem before disaster befalls them all?

episodes.title: Kemono Hime no Rhapsody
episodes.plot: The Cassuls arrive at the sea, only to be captured by a group of people living in a futuristic fortress. They seem to know a lot about the Scrapped Princess, and Zefiris soon uncovers the secret behind their technology.

episodes.title: Futari no Hime no Ikusauta
episodes.plot: While Princess and Guardians learn about nature of this world fleet of ships appear. They are led buy Peacemaker and they are attacking Princess Seness. Soon Peacemaker realize Scrapped Princess is there too, as well as 2 Dragoons.

episodes.title: Harukanaru Ricordanza
episodes.plot: Princess Senes and the Cassuls plan their next move against the Peacemakers. While the siblings catch up on ancient history, the Dragoons halt the fortress's advance. Is Pacifica's true power more important than thousands of lives?

episodes.title: Ushinawareta Quintet
episodes.plot: Zefiris explain her history to Pacifika. At the same time Natalie is trying to brain wash Shannon. Raquel and Seness are trying to start ships engines.

episodes.title: Chikara to Bouryaku no Opera
episodes.plot: The Royal Forces prepare to cast a sinister spell on Scarlet while Peacemakers loom overhead and destroy their fortress's defense system. When it comes down to a matter of fight or flight, can Shannon rely on Zefiris and face a familiar foe?

episodes.title: Kawa no Hotori no Duet
episodes.plot: Unconvinced of her death, friends and enemies in the capital of Leinwan are searching for the Scrapped Princess. But Pacifica has completely lost her memory and has begun a peaceful life with a kind stranger. Is she better off not remembering the truth?

episodes.title: Tsuka no Ma no Chanson
episodes.plot: The search for the Scrapped Princess has intensified, and while Chris's unit is ordered to join in the search, Cz causes trouble for Shannon. As enemies close in, Pacifica's friends come to warn her-but they may just be too late.

episodes.title: Roji Ura no Elegy
episodes.plot: Pacifica and her friends are on the run, but they need to steal horses if they want to leave the city. Leo and Furet finally get their hands on the reins when the Royal Forces catch up to them. To make matters worse, Chris's unit makes their next move.

episodes.title: Haha no Nageki no Aria
episodes.plot: Captured by the Royal Forces, Pacifica is thrown into the dungeon where she meets a fellow prisoner. Meanwhile, the General tries to recruit Shannon to assist in his endeavors of conquering Giat.

episodes.title: Seinaru Houkai no Overture
episodes.plot: Orders have been given to kill the Scrapped Princess, but Shannon won't stand for it. When Steyr unveils her sinister plan, all of humanity is threatened. Does Shannon have the power to fight the Peacemakers?

episodes.title: Kodoku na Kami no Junankyoku
episodes.plot: While Shannon and the Gigases wage battle with the Peacemakers, Chris's unit takes matters into its own hands. The city suffers great damage, and after friends are reunited, one grim question remains for Pacifica.

episodes.title: Toki o Koeta Rondo
episodes.plot: The Cassuls and their allies make camp and enjoy a short time of peace, when a mysterious woman appears before Pacifica with a cryptic tale. The rest of the world braces for the Scrapped Princess's birthday, now just three days away.

episodes.title: Kagiriaru Mono no Oratorio
episodes.plot: Military scouts found Pacifica's camp. All army forces are gathering for attack. Chris visits prince Forsyth.

episodes.title: Mamorishi Mono-tachi no Symphony
episodes.plot: The fight reaches its peak as Pacifica's end draws near. In another dimension, Lord Mauser offers a choice that could change the world forever.
